# midithrough: auto-detect (value 10 on a from* jack) uses the first port that
# actually sends events. Manual midithrough.md lines 55-58 ("If you specify
# fromusb = 10 or fromtrs = 10, the first port that actually sends events is
# used as input") and Inputs table lines 110-111 (fromtrs/fromusb = 10 enables
# auto detection). In the MASTER+X7 config there is exactly one TRS and one USB
# port, so auto-detect resolves to that single port of each type: a TRS-sourced
# event and a USB-sourced event are both forwarded to the target.
patch <<<
[midithrough]
    fromtrs = 10
    fromusb = 10
    totrs = 1
>>>
@0 midisend trs noteon 1 60 100
@0 expectmidi trs noteon 1 60 100
@0 expectmidi trs none
@1 midisend usb noteon 2 64 80
@1 expectmidi trs noteon 2 64 80
@1 expectmidi trs none
